item.title: You Cannot Teleport above level 20 wilderness
item.dc:creator: @Clawz_fury lare69
item.description:
@Clawz_fury wrote:

if you are using delta, then use the triggerTele(abs x, abs y, height); method, rather then using toX = x; and toY = y; If you use the triggerTele method, the method states that you can’t tele above 20 wilderness

[quote=“Dhfhy1, post:1, topic:372408”][code]I want to make it so only me and one other person can teleport above level 20 wilderness this is my client.java code, how do I add an exception to it ?

if(wildyLevel > 20 && isInWilderness(absX, absY, 1)){ sM("You cannot teleport above level 20 wilderness!"); return; } [/quote]

Aha,

if(wildyLevel > 20 && isInWilderness(absX, absY, 1) && !playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("otherperson") && !playerName.equalsIgnoreCase("you")){ sM("You cannot teleport above level 20 wilderness!"); return;

try that?
